Implemented the controller behavior in `components/controller/controller.c` and kept the public interface intact.

What’s covered:
- safe all-off boot state
- wait for both sensors before control
- fill below 60
- heat only in 60–75 with low temp
- hold/early-off behavior near 45–48
- hard safe-off above 48 / on malformed input / on timeout
- stale-sensor safety timeout handling

Visible verification added:
- `agent_tests/test_controller_uart.py`
  - firmware-level UART end-to-end nominal fill→heat→early-off probe
  - malformed input and stale timeout safety probe

Validation run:
- `python3 tools/run_build.py` ✅
- `python3 tools/run_self_tests.py` ✅
- `python3 tools/run_eval.py` ✅ submitted twice; latest submission recorded


